nodes.text: You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.
You have given Vault City a donation... for whatever it's worth.
It's down on the 3rd level, if I remember correctly. Haven't been down there in ages.
Oh! Hello, again.
Oh, no, no... you see, our pregnancies don't result from intercourse.
I'm . Mind if I ask you some questions?
Hmmph. I'm too busy to speak to you right now. If you need anything, see Dr. Troy.
You have convinced Phyllis to speak to Dr. Troy about the potential sterility in Vault City.
Look, I know you're a new Citizen and all, and I don't mean to throw a damper on your Citizenship, but this City can be VERY dull at times.
We don't see many new faces around here. I'm Phyllis. What's your name?
YES, MARTIN. GO - BOTTOM - LEVEL.
How would that happen?
Uh... hmmm. Listen to me again, closely this time: YOU - GO - MARTIN.

Oh, I don't know. Not much reason to go down into the Vault. It's mostly used for storage space nowadays. The only one down there is Martin, and... well, just between you and me, he's not a great conversationalist.
A ghoul! Aieeeeee! Guards!
You have convinced Phyllis to see the outside world.

Well, actually... you see, this is something I've been thinking about recently, but Citizens don't seem to have accidental pregnancies. The only successful pregnancies have been facilitated by the Auto-Doc.
Pardon me?
You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.
Guards! Dr. Troy! Help!
I'm sorry, but no.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
We don't see many new faces around here. I'm Phyllis. What's your name?
Yeah, it can get kind of overwhelming at times. But here I am, bringing down your opinion of Vault City. Don't misunderstand me. It's a great place to live.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
You risked your own life to save us ALL. You're the bravest person I've ever known.
Of course. What is it you would like to know?
Uh... maybe you SHOULD go speak to him. You two may have more in common than I first thought.
Well... yes. Actually, there aren't. Yet. I don't know if anyone told you yet, Vault City is a planned community. We're not due for another pregnancy cycle until a few years from now.
Oh my, you are hurt, aren't you? I'm sorry, I should have been paying more attention. Go see Dr. Troy. He'll take care of you.
An intruder! Aieeeeee! Guards!
GO - BOTTOM - LEVEL. LEVEL - THREE. NOW.
You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.

It's like they're all... clones. They all dress alike, act alike, and the worst part is that everybody seems happy with it. I... well, sometimes I worry that I'll end up being just like them. That probably sounds silly, huh?
Thanks for the wonderful evening.
Certainly. We'd welcome your contribution. Vault City could use some fresh genetic material.
Oh. Well, I... I'd love to.
Vault City? Well, actually, there's not much to say. I mean, I've been a Citizen all my life... but there's not much to do in Vault City. At all.
You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.
Oh, you mean intercourse? Intercourse is still allowed outside of pregnancy cycles.
Why, of all the...! I have NEVER met someone as low-class as yourself. I suggest you leave. Now.

I mean, have you noticed how similar everyone is? And OLD? Most of the seminars and extracurricular activities are geared towards octogenarians. I'm barely twenty-five, and this city makes me feel like I'm fifty.
You have given Vault City a donation and introduced favorable genetic material into their community.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
My name's . What do you do around here?
Are you certain? That doesn't sound like Dr. Troy at all. Still... he HAS been working hard lately... no, no, that's impossible. You must be mistaken.
Hmmm. Maybe your contribution wasn't as valuable as I thought. Thanks anyway, though.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
Male Citizens "donate" to the Auto-Doc here in the Vault and the most favorable matches are chosen by the computer. Then the appropriate female Citizen is seeded by the Auto-Doc.
Excellent! Thank you.
You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.
You have given Vault City a donation and introduced fresh genetic material into their community.
You see the Resident Medical Assistant, Phyllis.
A mutant! Aieeeeee! Guards!
Yes. Pregnancies are permitted only during certain years established by the Council.
I would be VERY careful about what you say about Dr. Troy in Vault City. He is a respected member of our community.
Uh no… "octogenerian" is an adjective that refers to a person who is eighty years old.
Oh, Dr. Troy can be pretty strict sometimes, but all in all, he's a good man. Vault City's fortunate to have him.
Uh... sure. Maybe we'll go out some other time. I'll... uh, call you. Bye.
I'm the Resident Medical Assistant. I work for Dr. Troy.
Well, welcome to Vault City, fellow Citizen.
You see a thin young woman. She smells faintly of antiseptic.
Well, I've been tempted to go outside the gate, but the other Citizens have warned me against it...
